@John Peil 

You’re welcome. 

I saw “The Sting” when it came out and had never heard a con game referred to as a sting. It stuck in my head, along with all that wonderful Scott Joplin music.

@Jack McCullough 

Not exactly.  When it's TSAR, it's always going to refer to the Russian monarch, because that spelling has no other meaning.  But when it's CZAR, it might be clued either way.  In the past decade, it has been clued to the Russian ruler 14 out of 30 times (if I counted right).

The government official (or titan of industry) will always be CZAR, but the Russian autocrat can be either.

@sotto voce 

Thanks for the video. It is, of course, unfair that one man should be gifted with such talent, beauty and as I think the kids say, "rizz." But good for him and us too. Saw him in PDX years ago with K. D Lang opening. What a great concert!

Love you comments, and oh yeah, nice puzzle ACM and Daniel!

@CCNY 

You did better than I! I was solving late-night and decided to count backwards from 26/Z, also on my fingers. Needless to say, my brain doesn't work that way very well! Took me three tries... and then I felt like a dolt, haha. 


